spec: multiprocessing_extra52
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(multiprocessing)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html — Python multiprocessing module documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.Process — Process documentation"
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/multiprocessing.html#multiprocessing.pool.Pool — Pool documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/process.py"
    - "CPython source: Lib/multiprocessing/context.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec extends multiprocessing_extra51.zspec.zsdl."
    - "Prior specs covered: Process/Queue/Pool/Lock/Event/Semaphore/Value/Array __name__/__module__, Process.__bases__[0].__name__=='BaseProcess', Process.__qualname__, ProcessError/AuthenticationError/BufferTooShort/TimeoutError identity and bases, cpu_count/get_start_method/set_start_method/get_context/active_children/__qualname__, exception __module__ and __len__(), context-bound class __qualname__.__len__() tables, Process method __qualname__.__len__() tables, Pool method qualname tables, Process/Pool __mro__.__len__() tables, __all__ metadata, class __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__() tables (extra29/extra30/extra32: lengths only), DefaultContext method qualname lengths, BaseProcess metadata, function __name__.__len__() tables, pool result class tables, Process/__name__=='Process', Pool/__name__=='Pool', Pool/__module__=='multiprocessing.pool', Pool/__qualname__=='Pool' (extra5/extra13/extra24), Pool/__bases__[0].__name__=='object', Pool/__mro__.__len__()==2, cpu_count/__module__==multiprocessing, Process method __qualname__ string equality, function __name__/__module__ equality, AuthenticationError/__name__/__module__/__bases__[0].__name__, ProcessError/__name__/__bases__[0].__name__, exception subclass MRO depths, class/function qualname string equality tables, context class tables, class __class__.__name__/__qualname__ tables, Pool/__doc__/__class__ tables, Pool/__name__.__len__()==4 (extra50), Pool/__module__.__len__()==20 (extra50), Pool.apply/map/starmap/apply_async/map_async/close/terminate/join __qualname__.__len__()/string equality (extra51), Process.__init__.__qualname__=='BaseProcess.__init__' (extra49)."
    - "This spec covers: multiprocessing class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality ('mappingproxy') for Process/Pool/ProcessError/AuthenticationError — prior specs (extra29/extra30/extra32) captured only __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra52 captures the full string equality in the mpdict52 namespace. Also: Process/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ and Pool/__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality ('mappingproxy'). Also: current_process/__qualname__.__len__()==15 and active_children/__qualname__.__len__()==15 cross-checks. Also: Pool/__qualname__.__len__()==4 cross-check (Pool.__qualname__=='Pool' was already covered in extra5/extra13/extra24)."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy — a read-only view of the class namespace dictionary. Process is defined in Lib/multiprocessing/process.py; its __dict__ has __class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars). Prior specs (extra29/extra32) captured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra52 captures the string equality in the mpdict52 namespace. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Pool.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Pool is defined in Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra30 captured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12; extra52 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. ProcessError is the base exception class in multiprocessing.context; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra29 captured __len__()==12; extra52 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy'. AuthenticationError is an exception class in multiprocessing.context; its __dict__ is a mappingproxy. Prior extra29 captured __len__()==12; extra52 captures the string equality. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Process.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. The mappingproxy type is a built-in type with no enclosing class or function scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. No prior multiprocessing spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__; extra52 opens this dimension. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.Pool.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'. Same reasoning as Process: mappingproxy is a built-in type with __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. Novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Pool. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.current_process.__qualname__.__len__() == 15. 'current_process' has 15 characters: c-u-r-r-e-n-t-_-p-r-o-c-e-s-s = 15. Prior specs captured current_process/__class__.__qualname__=='function' (extra-) and current_process/__name__.__len__()==15 (extra32) but not __qualname__.__len__()==15 in the mpdict52 namespace. For a module-level function, __qualname__ == __name__. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "multiprocessing.active_children.__qualname__.__len__() == 15. 'active_children' has 15 characters: a-c-t-i-v-e-_-c-h-i-l-d-r-e-n = 15. Prior specs captured __qualname__ string equality (extra-) but extra52 cross-checks __qualname__.__len__()==15 in the mpdict52 namespace. Verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-10."
  created_at: "2026-04-10T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality — extra52
#
# Every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy, a read-only view of the class
# namespace dictionary. The mappingproxy type has:
#   __class__.__name__     == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#   __class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy'  (12 chars)
#
# Prior specs (extra29/extra30/extra32) measured __dict__.__class__.__name__.__len__()==12
# for several multiprocessing classes but never the 'mappingproxy' string equality.
# Extra52 introduces the string equality checks in the mpdict52 namespace for:
#   Process, Pool, ProcessError, AuthenticationError
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra52.class_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing class __dict__.__class__.__name__ string equality in extra52 namespace — all class __dict__ objects are mappingproxy instances; prior specs captured __len__()==12 only"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mpdict52clsname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Process,             Process.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,             ["mappingproxy"], true, "Process.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is always a mappingproxy in CPython; prior extra29/extra32 captured __len__()==12 but not the string equality"]
    - [Pool,                Pool.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,                ["mappingproxy"], true, "Pool.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — defined in Lib/multiprocessing/pool.py; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra30 captured __len__()==12"]
    - [ProcessError,        ProcessError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__,        ["mappingproxy"], true, "ProcessError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — base exception class in multiprocessing.context; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra29 captured __len__()==12"]
    - [AuthenticationError, AuthenticationError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "AuthenticationError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class in multiprocessing.context; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra29 captured __len__()==12"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality — extra52
#
# The mappingproxy type is a built-in type with no enclosing class or function
# scope, so __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'. No prior multiprocessing
# spec has captured __dict__.__class__.__qualname__. Extra52 covers Process and
# Pool as representative cases.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra52.class_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing class __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ string equality in extra52 namespace — mappingproxy has __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: class_names
  id_prefix: mpdict52clsqualname

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [Process, Process.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__, ["mappingproxy"], true, "Process.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type with no enclosing scope; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); first __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check in multiprocessing specs"]
    - [Pool,    Pool.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__,    ["mappingproxy"], true, "Pool.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — built-in mappingproxy type; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'; novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Pool"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing function __qualname__.__len__() cross-checks — extra52
#
# current_process and active_children are module-level functions in
# multiprocessing. For module-level functions, __qualname__ == __name__.
#
#   current_process.__qualname__.__len__() == 15  ('current_process' = 15 chars)
#   active_children.__qualname__.__len__() == 15  ('active_children' = 15 chars)
#
# Prior specs captured __qualname__ string equality for these functions
# and __name__.__len__()==15. Extra52 cross-checks __qualname__.__len__()==15.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table multiprocessing_extra52.function_qualname_len:
  description: "multiprocessing function __qualname__.__len__() cross-check in extra52 namespace — current_process and active_children are module-level functions with __qualname__==__name__"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: module_identity
  id_prefix: mpdict52funcqualnamelen

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [current_process, current_process.__qualname__.__len__, [], 15, "current_process.__qualname__.__len__() == 15 — 'current_process' has 15 characters; module-level function has __qualname__ == __name__ == 'current_process'"]
    - [active_children, active_children.__qualname__.__len__, [], 15, "active_children.__qualname__.__len__() == 15 — 'active_children' has 15 characters; module-level function has __qualname__ == __name__ == 'active_children'"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# multiprocessing.Pool __qualname__.__len__() cross-check — extra52
#
# Pool.__qualname__ == 'Pool' (4 chars). Prior specs captured:
#   Pool.__qualname__ == 'Pool' (extra5/extra13/extra24)
#   Pool.__name__.__len__() == 4 (extra50)
# Extra52 adds the complementary __qualname__.__len__()==4 cross-check.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.Pool_qualname_len:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pool.__qualname__.__len__() == 4 — 'Pool' has 4 characters; cross-check for Pool.__qualname__=='Pool' from extra5/extra13/extra24; equals Pool.__name__.__len__()==4 from extra50 since Pool is a top-level class"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pool.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 4

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Standalone invariants — extra52
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.Process_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — every Python class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; 'mappingproxy' is 12 chars; prior extra29/extra32 captured __len__()==12, extra52 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.Pool_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pool.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra30 captured __len__()==12, extra52 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pool.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.ProcessError_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.ProcessError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — base exception class; class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra29 captured __len__()==12, extra52 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: ProcessError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.AuthenticationError_dict_class_name_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.AuthenticationError.__dict__.__class__.__name__ == 'mappingproxy' — exception class __dict__ is a mappingproxy; prior extra29 captured __len__()==12, extra52 adds the string equality"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: AuthenticationError.__dict__.__class__.__name__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.Process_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Process.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type with no enclosing scope; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy' (12 chars); first __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check in multiprocessing specs"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Process.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.Pool_dict_class_qualname_eq:
  description: "multiprocessing.Pool.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__ == 'mappingproxy' — mappingproxy is a built-in type; __qualname__ == __name__ == 'mappingproxy'; novel __dict__.__class__.__qualname__ check for Pool"
  category: class_names
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: Pool.__dict__.__class__.__qualname__.__eq__
  args: ["mappingproxy"]
  expected: true

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.current_process_qualname_len:
  description: "multiprocessing.current_process.__qualname__.__len__() == 15 — 'current_process' has 15 characters; module-level function has __qualname__ == __name__; cross-check for __qualname__=='current_process' from prior specs"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: current_process.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 15

invariant multiprocessing_extra52.active_children_qualname_len:
  description: "multiprocessing.active_children.__qualname__.__len__() == 15 — 'active_children' has 15 characters; module-level function has __qualname__ == __name__; cross-check for __qualname__=='active_children' from prior specs"
  category: module_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: active_children.__qualname__.__len__
  args: []
  expected: 15
